originalTitle: South Africa and Israel expel each other's envoys in diplomatic row
title: South Africa and Israel expel each other's envoys in diplomatic row
content: South Africa accuses the Israeli envoy of insulting President Ramaphosa. Israel says the expulsion is "baseless".

originalTitle: Music legend Fela Kuti becomes first African to get Grammys Lifetime Achievement Award
title: Music legend Fela Kuti becomes first African to get Grammys Lifetime Achievement Award
content: Almost 30 years after he died, the Nigerian will posthumously receive a Lifetime Achievement Award.

originalTitle: Burkina Faso junta announces ban on all political parties
title: Burkina Faso junta announces ban on all political parties
content: The multiparty system had been "promoting division among citizens", the country's interior minister said.

title: Djokovic beats Sinner as history and Alcaraz await in Australian Open final
content: Novak Djokovic stuns reigning two-time champion Jannik Sinner to set up Australian Open final against Carlos Alcaraz.

originalTitle: Trump nominates Kevin Warsh to replace Powell as fed chair
title: Trump nominates Kevin Warsh to replace Powell as fed chair
content: Nomination comes as Trump heaps pressure on Powell to cut interest rates; Warsh to face challenging Senate confirmation.

originalTitle: US-Iran tensions: The diplomatic scramble to prevent a war
title: US-Iran tensions: The diplomatic scramble to prevent a war
content: Facing the prospect of US strikes, Iran has intensified diplomatic efforts with countries including Turkiye.

title: Former CNN host Don Lemon arrested after anti-ICE protests at Minnesota church
content: Lemon says he was just doing his job as a journalist reporting on the protests at the church.

title: Syrian government reaches deal with Kurdish-led forces
content: The deal will see the gradual integration of Kurdish forces and administration into the Syrian state.

title: Trump tells Iran to drop nuclear aims and stop killing protesters to avoid military action
content: Iran's Foreign Minister Araghchi says armed forces had "fingers on the trigger" to respond to any US strike.

title: Benfica meet Real in play-offs after dramatic league phase encounter

title: Celtic to play Stuttgart & Forest face Fenerbahce in Europa play-offs

title: Mateta 'not in right place' to play against Forest
content: Crystal Palace striker Jean-Philippe Mateta is "not in the right place" to play against Nottingham Forest as he continues to be linked with a move away, says Oliver Glasner.
